# plan/facts/24-graded-practitioner-receipts.bn
#
# Less-credible-but-graded sources from 2026-05-03 research pass.
# Each is scored per facts/23 5-axis rubric (S/C/D/I/V → 0-15) before
# composition. Sources at L4 (12-15) are load-bearing; L5 (9-11) are
# composable as supporting input; L6 (6-8) recorded but NOT composed.
#
# Per facts/23 anti-gullibility floor: L4-L6 sources LIFT MARGIN, never
# replace L1-L3 foundation. Composition with M3.x own-measurement +
# facts/14+18 research-mutawatir keeps these honest.

# ============================================================
# L4 PRACTITIONER-MUTAWATIR sources (load-bearing)
# ============================================================

# G1 — Anthropic publicly DOUBLED Claude Code dev cost estimate
# (S=3 production data, C=3 exact numbers, D=3 vendor admits prior
# estimate was low, I=3 adversarial — vendor admitting against own
# preference, V=3 confirmed across multiple outlets).
# Score: 15/15 — L4 max.
# Content: $13/active-day, $150-250/dev/month. 90% of users below
# $30/active-day. Prior estimate $6/active-day pre-2026-04-16.
# IMPLICATION for cheapcode: real-world frontier-only Claude Code
# costs are HIGH and increasing — cost-dominance headroom is large.
lemma g1_anthropic_doubles_claude_code_cost_estimate_to_13_per_active_day_l4_max
  proves True
  by audit anthropic-cost-doubling-2026-04-16-fetched-2026-05-03

# G2 — Simon Willison's tracking of Claude Code costs and workflows
# (S=3 production blog 3+ yr, C=3 specific numbers, D=3 long
# calibration record, I=2 independent practitioner, V=2 corroborated
# by HN). Score: 13/15 — L4.
# Content: confusion about pricing models; transparency about own
# experience; admits when uncertain; cites specific dollar amounts.
lemma g2_simonw_claude_code_cost_confusion_2026_04_22_l4
  proves True
  by audit simonwillison-net-2026-04-22-claude-code-confusion

# G3 — HN "Staff engineer's journey with Claude Code" + similar threads
# (S=3 staff-engineer at production company, C=2-3 specific dollar
# amounts $0.04/PR-review × 200+ PRs = $19.50 in Feb on Opus 4.6,
# D=2 admits both wins and failures, I=2 independent, V=3 multiple
# HN threads converging). Score: 12-13/15 — L4.
# Content: Real production teams using Claude Code-class harnesses
# at $0.04 per code-review with 2 review rounds each = $19.50/month
# for 200+ PRs.
lemma g3_hn_staff_engineer_claude_code_19_50_per_month_200_prs_l4
  proves True
  by audit news-ycombinator-com-45107962-fetched-2026-05-03

# G4 — opencode GitHub issues #16367 / #14972 / #20387
# (S=3 production users, C=3 reproducible repros with file paths +
# error messages, D=3 explicit failure-mode descriptions, I=3
# adversarial — filing bugs costs time and damages relationships
# with tool one depends on, V=2 multiple converging issues).
# Score: 14/15 — L4.
# Content load-bearing for Phase II-prime substrate-harness wiring:
#   #16367: agent silent-hang on permission "ask" + opencode-attach
#           (server waits for UI prompt that doesn't exist on remote)
#   #14972: agent loop exits prematurely with OpenAI-compat providers
#           because finish_reason="stop" not "tool-calls"
#   #20387: plugin hooks cannot spawn AI sub-agent (no "type":"agent"
#           hook); blocks Claude-Code-style hook patterns
# Phase II-prime substrate-harness work MUST address these specific
# failure modes — they are the empirical specification of where
# substrate signals would compose with the inherited harness.
lemma g4_opencode_gh_issues_16367_14972_20387_l4_phase_ii_prime_specification
  proves True
  by audit github-anomalyco-opencode-issues-16367-14972-20387-fetched-2026-05-03

